<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>88</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975110150</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
q Saturday: Aberdeen and District Motor Club's Williamson Rally, an event of
long standing, starts in the evening from Hatton, and brings the East of
Scotland rally championship to a close for another year.
q Sunday: West of Scotland Kart Club finishes its racing season with a meeting
at the Summerlee Raceway, Larkhall. There are no more kart races on Scottish
circuits during 1995.
q Sunday: Marking the end of a series of forest rallies which began in February
with the Snowman, the South-West Saab Galloway Hills Rally virtually takes over
Gatehouse of Fleet for the day.
Although it comes after the end of the Scottish Rally Championship, it usually
attracts a fine entry of both Scottish and Irish crews, being convenient for
the ferries at Stranraer and Cairnryan.
The organisers always manage to provide a very compact route. This year, the
first car leaves Gatehouse at 09.30 and should be back at the finish within
four hours or so. There are five forest stages totalling about 40 miles. Most
of the action is around Clatteringshaws and Cairn Edward, but this time there
is also a stage at Glengap.
Prize-giving is at the Murray Arms around 16.00.
</TEXT>
