<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>41</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975110156</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
q RANGERS keeper Andy Goram has been named Scotland's top player for November,
while Scotland coach Craig Brown, who guided his side into the European
Championship finals, has been named as Bell's Manager of the Month.
Goram's Player of the Month award comes on the strength of good displays in
recent club games against Celtic and Steaua Bucharest as he returned from a
three-match injury absence.
The Young Player of the Month award went to Aberdeen midfielder Stephen Glass,
while Raith manager Jimmy Nicholl collected the Premier Manager of the Month
award.
</TEXT>
