<HEADLINE>Nobilo's classic birdie blast</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>40</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975110168</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
NEW Zealander Frank Nobilo charged home with six straight birdies for a course
record 64, and a one-shot lead, in the first round of the Greg Norman Classic
in Sydney yesterday.
On the way to his nine-under-par score, Nobilo played the treacherous back nine
at the testing par-73 The Lakes course in a seven-under 30.
Australian Craig Parry, playing in tougher late afternoon conditions, also
mounted a birdie charge over the closing holes for an eight-under 65 and second
place.
Parry picked up four shots in the closing five holes, including holing a bunker
shot for an eagle 3 at the fourteenth.
Nobilo's fellow New Zealanders, Grant Waite and Michael Campbell, share third
place at seven under.
Tournament host and world No.1 Greg Norman, fresh from victory in the
Australian Open last week, is eight shots adrift. Norman held the previous
record of 64 at the venue, set in 1978 on a different, par-72, layout.
Open champion John Daly, partnering Norman and Nobilo, shot a one-over 74 to be
10 shots off the pace. Leading scores (Australian unless stated):
64 - F Nobilo (New Zealand).
