<DOC>
<DOCNO>GH951201-000030</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH951201-000030</DOCID>
<DATE>951201</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Palmer debut</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>41</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975110176</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
TENNIS
AMERICA-based Philippa Palmer who last month took advantage of her Scottish
roots to make her debut in the Guardian Direct national championships in
Telford, will make her first appearance for the East of Scotland women's team
in this weekend's British Inter-County Championships.
The three-day event opens today at 21 venues across Britain and in the absence
of Scottish No.1, Michele Mair, Edinburgh-born Palmer, the world No.825, will
lead East against Devon, Kent, and Berkshire in Group 4B at Exmouth.
The Gannochy Centre in Stirling will host women's Group 3A while West and South
clash in Group 5B at Newcastle along with Avon and Worcestershire.
</TEXT>
