<HEADLINE>Five players come off the rails</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>37</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975110179</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
FIVE Steaua Bucharest players have been banned for two years for attacking a
linesman on a train, the Romanian Rugby Union Federation have said.
``The Steaua players were punished because such behaviour is unacceptable,''
said FRR general secretary Sorin Fuicu. Earlier this month Steaua lost their
lead in the domestic rugby union championship after having gone down 6-3 in a
match at Universitatea Baia Mare.
On their return trip to Bucharest, the five Steaua players struck one of the
linesmen who happened to be on the same train.
The five men - Nicolae Dragos, Leodor Costea, Lucian Colceriu, Marius Nedelcu,
and Costica Florea - have played for Romania's national team in the past few
years.
``They are not only banned from playing in Romania, but also in any country
affiliated to the International Rugby Union Board,'' Fuicu said.
q.MILAN and Italian internationalist flanker Massimo Giovanelli has been given
a 60-day ban for headbutting in a European Cup match against the Welsh side,
Pontypridd, last month.
The Italian rugby federation said the ban was handed down by the cup organisers
for the incident on November 22. It means Giovanelli will miss six matches up
to January 20.
Milan lost to Pontypridd    31-12, ending their hopes of progress in the
inaugural European Cup.
</TEXT>
