<DOCNO>GH951201-000043</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH951201-000043</DOCID>
<DATE>951201</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Kwik-Fit deal</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>KRISTY DORSEY</BYLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>22</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975110189</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
CAR parts replacement giant Kwik-Fit is set to expand with its #12m cash
purchase of Birmingham-based Tyre Sales, the largest tyre and automotive repair
company in the Midlands region.
The newly-acquired subsidiary's 43 retail centres and 40,000 square foot
wholesale warehouse will continue to operate under the Tyre Sales logo.
In the year to November 30, 1994, the company produced pre-tax profits of
#200,000 on a turnover of #21.1m.
Tyre Sales' net assets at that date amounted to #2.2m, and net assets are not
expected to be lower than that figure when the acquisition is completed.
In the 11 months to October 1995, management accounts showed the Midlands
company's sales to be in line with the previous year. Profit for the same
period, before interest and directors' pay, amounted to #900,000.
A Kwik-Fit spokesman said the purchase of Tyre Sales would help increase
Kwik-Fit's representation in the Midlands, an area into which the company has
wanted to expand.
``There aren't too many regional chains of this size around, so Kwik-Fit was
quite pleased when this one came available and they were able to acquire it,''
he said.
He added that although there were no specific plans concerning future
purchases, he thought Kwik-Fit would ``certainly be interested'' if any more
Midlands automotive companies became available.
Over the medium to long-term, Kwik-Fit will be looking for improvement in Tyre
Sales' operating performance, the spokesman said. This will be done through
more effective marketing and employee training.
``There is a Kwik-Fit way of doing things and I'm sure the incoming management
will want to show the employees how Kwik-Fit operates,'' the spokesman said.
Kwik-Fit, Europe's largest independent car parts replacement company, will
operate out of 779 specialist fitting centres after the Tyre Sales purchase is
complete.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
