<DOCNO>GH951201-000053</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH951201-000053</DOCID>
<DATE>951201</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Prisoner on run from hospital</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<FLAG>news digest</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>975110199</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A MAN who was committed to the State Hospital at Carstairs without limit of
time more than 20 years ago after being charged with murder has absconded from
a Paisley hospital.
Robert Moor, 52, from Barrhead was transferred to Dykebar Hospital from
Carstairs to continue his rehabilitation in 1993. He was acquitted of murder in
1971.
Charge dropped
FOOTBALLER John Fashanu is not being charged with attempting to pervert the
course of justice, police said last night. A case alleging match rigging with
goalkeepers Bruce Grobbelaar and Hans Segers, and Malay businessman Heng Suan
Lim, is due for a second remand hearing in Southampton today.
Christmas cell
THE Benedictine monastery at Fort William is offering three-day Christmas
breaks. Its 15 monks offer B&amp;B in 40 rooms at #13.50 a night.
Jail warning
TWO brothers face prison for taking a 10-ton steam-roller and driving it
through the village of Cove on the Clyde coast, Sheriff John Fitzsimmons said
yesterday. Sentence was deferred until December 21 at Dumbarton Sheriff Court
on Scott Brydon, 23, of Strathcona Gardens, Glasgow, and Derek Brydon, 16, of
Stanmore Road, Glasgow, who both admitted taking the steam-roller.
Prisons chief
GENERAL Sir David Ramsbotham, 61, takes up the post of Chief Inspector of
Prisons today. He succeeds Judge Stephen Tumim.
Hearing date set
A SOLICITOR who represented Frederick West has been ordered to attend a
disciplinary tribunal in London on February 29 over an allegation that he tried
to sell West's life story in a #1m deal. Mr Howard Ogden, who is based in
Cheltenham, denies the charge.
Mild but wet
BRITAIN enjoyed its mildest autumn since records began some 300 years ago, the
Met Office said yesterday. But Scotland had 611mm - over 2ft - of rain during
the season, well above the 449mm (17.7in) average.
Crash death
A YOUNG man died and another was seriously injured yesterday when two cars were
involved in an accident on the A80 Glasgow to Cumbernauld road, just north of
the Stepps roundabout.
Yarrow boost
YARROW Shipbuilders on the Clyde has secured a multi-million pound export order
from Brunei for three patrol boats but work on the contract is not expected to
start for another year.
</TEXT>
