<HEADLINE>GA deputy chief dies</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>23</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>obituary</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>975110353</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
BARRIE Holder, deputy chief executive and finance director of General Accident,
died suddenly yesterday during a visit to London.
A spokesman for the Perth-based insurance company said he believed Mr Holder,
who was aged 50, had suffered a heart attack.
Mr Holder was responsible for finance, investment and life assurance at General
Accident and pushed through its #170m takeover of Provident Mutual earlier this
year.
Originally from Yorkshire, he was a rising star with the company. He was
appointed general manager and a member of the board in 1990 and was promoted to
deputy chief executive last year.
General Accident chief executive Nelson Robertson is due to retire at the end
of this year to be replaced by Bob Scott, the company's other deputy chief
executive.
</TEXT>
