<HEADLINE>Student welcome</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>10</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975110371</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
OVERSEAS students at the University of Abertay, Dundee, will be invited into
local people's homes under a scheme launched yesterday by the university and
Dundee Rotary club. The scheme will give students an insight into the business
world and a chance to take part in family activities.
Insurance win
A HOSPITAL doctor who lives in County Durham has won a #220,000 pay-out from
two insurance companies which claimed he intentionally chopped off part of a
thumb and index finger to gain insurance money.
Shoppers sought
TWO women who loaded goods worth #944 from a supermarket trolley into a car at
Southend, Essex, then drove off without paying were being hunted by police
yesterday.
</TEXT>
