<TEXT>
Drug pact made
BRUSSELS: The European Union has reached the first of a series of agreements it
hopes will control the use of legal chemicals used to make illegal and
addictive drugs such as cocaine, ecstasy, and heroin. The EU hopes the accord
with the five-nation Andean Pact, which lies at the centre of the international
drugs trade in Latin America, will be followed by others on the American
continent and in Asia.
Banda case rests
BLANTYRE: The prosecution has rested in the murder trial of Malawi's former
president Kamuzu Banda after more than 100 witnesses testified. The defence is
expected to call its first witness on Monday in the trial which began on July
10.
Guernica naked
MADRID: Bullet-proof glass has been removed from artist Pablo Picasso's war
masterpiece Guernica, lifting security in place since the controversial work
came to the country in 1981. The vast 1937 canvas depicts the Nazi bombing of
the Basque city Guernica during Spain's civil war. Culture Minister Carmen
Alborch said the young Spanish democracy had matured enough to display the
painting ``naked and as it is''.
</TEXT>
