<HEADLINE>Unhamper yourself with festive fare</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>LOUDON TEMPLE</BYLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>16</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975110378</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SCOTS supercook Mo Scott will be busier than most in the run-up to Christmas as
she slaves over a hot stove in her Renfrewshire farmhouse kitchen. Sometimes
she finds it hard to keep the festive spirit alive . . . for she has built up
such a reputation for her fine cooking that, come this time of year, she is
inundated with requests for homemade produce.
Mention mince pie and she's guaranteed to wince. Last year, she turned out 2300
before Christmas Day. This year, she expects five thousand hand-made pies to
leave her oven. Since running Glasgow's successful Poachers Restaurant - a
stint which kept her occupied for eight years, until she set up her own
Earlshill Farm Foods business almost two years ago - she has made quite a name
for herself, producing fine cuisine and gourmet food.
A mouth-watering range of pre-packed meals, all made with fresh ingredients and
no preservatives, additives or colourings, has customers hooked as far away as
London. This year, Scott has put together two attractive gourmet hampers, #30
and #50.
A new item on her list of Christmas gift offers should prove a hit with people
from all walks of life. She says: ``We are offering gift vouchers for our
cookery demonstrations. These should hit the spot with women who want to get
rid of their men for an evening.
``It will be a bonus, too, if they return home with new skills to prove they
know their stuff.''
The cookery sessions take place in Scott's kitchen at Newton of Belltrees, near
Lochwinnoch. Each week the procession of satisfied customers making the trek to
her front door gets longer and longer.
The Earlshill Farm Foods Christmas selection contains Plum Pudding in two sizes
at #6.50 and #8.50; Mince Pies, #3.50 per dozen; Filo Canapes, #5 per dozen;
Christmas Freezer Packs at #50 and #100, and, of course those
beautifully-decorated wicker baskets full of delicious home-made goodies and a
half bottle of Muscat de Frontignan dessert wine. In the run-up to Christmas,
Scott will be staging cookery demonstrations for a Fireside Supper; The Cool,
Calm Christmas Lunch and The Breakneck Christmas Banquet. Telephone
01505-843434 for further information.
</TEXT>
