<DOCNO>GH951201-000128</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH951201-000128</DOCID>
<DATE>951201</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Baby Amy's mother traced</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975110398</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE mother of Amy, the baby girl who was found abandoned on the doorsteps of
Glasgow Royal Maternity Hospital, has been traced, Strathclyde Police announced
yesterday.
The woman, who is 42, has been interviewed and a report will be sent to the
procurator-fiscal.
Amy, as nurses called the baby, was found by hospital staff at 4am on Tuesday
November 21 after they had been alerted by a female caller. She was thought to
be between one and two hours old.
</TEXT>
